args:
When the guests gathered in the ritual hall are
slaughtered, the apostles are left to mount a
last-ditch fight against Basileus and Loki to stop
Satan's resurrection. But just as victory seems
to be within reach, Loki summons a new and
powerful demonic entity.
Try not to evade so predictably. Haaah!
Nnngh... It seems...this is as far as I go...
I'd hoped to hold out...a bit longer...\nbut you people are exhausting...
Target neutralized. If we have no further\ncause to linger, let's hurry on.
Agreed. We need to get to that\nritual hall yesterday.
Then...you aren't going to finish me?
If you kill me here, my Sigil's connection\nwill claim Basileus as well. If you aim to\nstop him, this is the easiest way.
Is that a feeble attempt to sway us?\nWell, we don't have time for it.\nEveryone run! NOW!
If you're sincere about atoning, Michael,\nthen you and Basileus need to live.\nDon't take the coward's way out by dying.
But I fear you all will come to regret\nthat decision...
Curia of the Ilian Church of Grams\nAugust Cathedral\nAuspecalia Ritual Hall
By the Goddess... This is a horror.
Such carnage...\nAre the 666 already dead, then?
Where is Origa? I know she was here!
Then I invite you to pick through the\ncorpses until you find who you're looking\nfor. Oh, but you might need some gloves.
My, my! The ever-composed Regina finally\nloses her cool. I'm lucky to have seen such\na rare sight before the end.
The end that is now upon us all.
Didn't you feel it the moment you stepped\ninto this place? The countdown to Satan's\nglorious rebirth is upon us!
Harle? ...No, you must be the impostor.\nWow, you did a really good job with that—\nI can barely make out any difference.

So you've met the real Harle? In that case,
I suppose it's time. Can't have you running
about just calling me ＂impostor＂ all the
livelong day, now can we?
From now on, you can just call me Loki.
I don't give a hoot WHAT you want to be\ncalled! I don't see Satan stomping around\nthis place, which means there's still time.
Depending on the effort, it's even possible\nthat you might prevent his resurrection\nfrom coming about.
More demonic entities? This isn't good.
None of that changes what we must do.\nWe take them down and stop Satan's\nrevival for good!
Then let's all do our part as hands\nof the Goddess! Sigil, release!
Time to pick up where we left off\nin Rozcimea, Basileus!
Hmph. If you're so eager to finish what\nwe started, I trust you've come up with\na countermeasure for...this?
Things won't be so easy for you this time;\nRegina's already analyzed your little toy\nand blocked its effects.
I should hope this would prove more of\na challenge than last time.
(We seem evenly matched, but they may\neven have a slight advantage after our\nall-out battle with Michael.)
(The longer this drags on, the worse\nit gets for us. Better finish it now!)
(Huh?! One of the demonic entities fell!\nI see. They mean to turn this from a brawl\ninto a series of small engagements.)

(...Loki seems aware of what they're
doing as well. In that case, I'll follow his
lead and stay put. We'll take them as they
come.)
(We aim for the moment they strike.\nWhen they come for what they believe is\na single target, they'll find two waiting!)
If you fancy keeping your head firmly\nmounted atop your shoulders, friend,\nthen I would advise you not to move.
And the real one appears! How exciting.\nHave you been acting alone all this while\njust to create this opportunity?
Glad my impostor at least has my smarts.\nLoki, was it? It's been just AGES.

I'm rather flattered to see you still wearing
my body all these years later. Not that I
can blame you, of course—I really am
something of a handsome devil.
In fact, I'm rather thankful, given present\ncircumstances. Pity for you, though.
Nice work, Harle! We'll manage fine so\nlong as you keep Basileus pinned down!
Aw, why so quiet? Has the sudden turn of\nevents left you speechless?
That's the last of the demonic entities!
Now only you remain, Loki. Surrender and\nrelinquish the Sacred Shard.
But this Shard contains the mana I need\nto summon Satan!
If I gave this up, all my plans to will be\nfoiled and the day will be saved.
Bow before might, as all lives must.\nThere can be no escape.
This little dear possesses power far greater\nthan the demonic entities you faced before.\nI trust you'll enjoy your time together!

I am the apostle Nevin, one tired and
very ticked-off hand of the Goddess,
and I WILL see her damn will done.
Sigil, release!
